ROOT (the ~85%-universal "FH loop_filter_level" class): the M0/M1
independent-uv search's fast-candidate sort. C sorts the SAD-ranked
(uv_mode, angle_delta) candidates with sort_fast_cost_based_candidates
(product_coding_loop.c:1415, ind-uv call :7680) — a swap-on-< selection
sort whose TIE order is not injection order. The port's bd8 arm used a
stable sort_by_key (bd10 already replicated C). Flat-chroma SAD tie
groups straddle the nfl=32 full-loop cut on nearly every real photo, so
the port full-evaluated a DIFFERENT candidate set, flipping a chroma
angle delta / uv mode somewhere mid-frame; the winner's chroma recon then
shifts every later chroma DC prediction, MD decisions cascade, and the
recon-driven deblock/CDEF/LR searches re-price -> the universal FH
loop_filter_level first-divergence symptom. The LF level was never the
bug.

Localization chain (drill cell cid22 1200348 q32 p0): drill_cell.sh ->
decode-diff --first-block-diff (first record flip mi(40,62) uv CfL-vs-D203;
records ignore angle deltas) -> tree_diff aduv flip mi(32,48) C=-3 port=0
(the true first coded flip) -> NSQDBG CFLARB (new) vs C SVT_UVLOOP_XY
per-candidate join: all inputs identical, C full-evaluates (V,-3) but
never (V,0), stable port the opposite -> the sort.

